l prepared for the next health crisis this timely book argues that the battle against infectious disease epidemics must be fought on two fronts the first of course is the laboratory the second is the wider social context that involves ordinary individuals and groups legislators and the state the failure to contain hiv aids and the emergence of new infectious diseases highlight the inadequacies of current preventive and management approaches to deal with epidemics the authors of crisis preparedness offer perspectives from social science epidemiology and public health collectively seeking to answer the question how can we prepare for the next global epidemic crisis preparedness asia and the global governance of epidemics stella quah ed chris beyrer kari hartwig gabriel m leung graham scambler jim whitman shorenstein aparc 2007 paperback 978 1 931368 09 4 $24.95 pdf+ crisis preparedness introduction by stella r quah june 2007 pdf 1_quah_final_cp2007 pdf 121.3 kb pdf+ crisis preparedness contributor bios june 2007 pdf contributors_final_cp2007 pdf 64.0 kb search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest charles perrow how we can prevent the worst april 7 2011 cisac announcement shorenstein aparc publishes final book in regionalism series september 22 2010 shorenstein aparc announcement shorenstein aparc announces new fellowships and faculty searches for the 2010 2011 academic year september 9 2009 shorenstein aparc news shorenstein aparc announces new shorenstein fellows for 2008 09 march 16 2008 shorenstein aparc news call for proposals shorenstein aparc establishes new fund for comparative health care policy research august 18 2005 shorenstein aparc news council on foreign relations publishes new book on america's climate change policy september 7 2004 pesd press release support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 6